    },
    {
      "uid": "sn14.31",
      "root_name": "Pubbesambodhasutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 14.31",
      "blurb": "Before his awakening the Buddha saw the gratification, the drawback, and the escape in the four material elements.",
      "node_type": "leaf",
      "root_lang_iso": "pli",
      "root_lang_name": "Pāli",
      "child_range": null,
      "yellow_brick_road": true,
      "yellow_brick_road_count": 2
    },
    {
      "uid": "sn14.32",
      "root_name": "Acariṁsutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 14.32",
      "blurb": "The Buddha set out to discover the gratification, the drawback, and the escape in the four material elements, and found it.",
      "node_type": "leaf",
      "root_lang_iso": "pli",
      "root_lang_name": "Pāli",
      "child_range": null,
      "yellow_brick_road": true,
      "yellow_brick_road_count": 2
    },
    {
      "uid": "sn14.33",
      "root_name": "Nocedaṁsutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 14.33",
      "blurb": "Each of the three aspects of the four material elements performs its own function. Gratification stimulates desire; drawbacks lead to disillusionment, while escape opens the possibility of freedom.",
      "node_type": "leaf",
      "root_lang_iso": "pli",
      "root_lang_name": "Pāli",
      "child_range": null,
      "yellow_brick_road": true,
      "yellow_brick_road_count": 2
    },
    {
      "uid": "sn14.34",
      "root_name": "Ekantadukkhasutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 14.34",
      "blurb": "If the material elements were solely painful, beings would not get attached. If they were solely pleasurable, it would be impossible to become detached. ",
      "node_type": "leaf",
      "root_lang_iso": "pli",
      "root_lang_name": "Pāli",
      "child_range": null,
      "yellow_brick_road": true,
      "yellow_brick_road_count": 2
    },
    {
      "uid": "sn14.35",
      "root_name": "Abhinandasutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 14.35",
      "blurb": "When you seek pleasure in the material elements, you seek pleasure in suffering.",
      "node_type": "leaf",
      "root_lang_iso": "pli",
      "root_lang_name": "Pāli",
      "child_range": null,
      "yellow_brick_road": true,
      "yellow_brick_road_count": 2
    },
    {
      "uid": "sn14.36",
      "root_name": "Uppādasutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 14.36",
      "blurb": "The arising of the material elements is the arising of suffering.",
      "node_type": "leaf",
      "root_lang_iso": "pli",
      "root_lang_name": "Pāli",
      "child_range": null,
      "yellow_brick_road": true,
      "yellow_brick_road_count": 2
    },
    {
      "uid": "sn14.37",
      "root_name": "Samaṇabrāhmaṇasutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 14.37",
